        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 2:20PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 219 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Macedonia, or near
Hiawassee, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Winds up to 40 mph and nickel sized hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Hiawassee, Young Harris, Whitley Gap Shelter, Blue Mountain Shelter,
Brasstown Bald, Titus, Mountain Scene, Low Gap Shelter, Owltown,
Track Rock, Tate City, Macedonia, and Plum Orchard Gap Shelter.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately.</instruction>
